 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO Reversing Tuesday’s weak start, the domestic bourse posted the biggest single day gain on Wednesday since 26 January 2022 as the benchmark index inched up 1.25% to close at 48,138.71 points, the highest point since 16 September 2008. Strong gains in index heavyweights, AIRTELAFRI (+4.73%), DANGCEM (+1.93%) and SEPLAT (+4.57%) reversed losses of the previous session, despite sustained profit taking in ZENITHBANK (-3.42%), GTCO (-3.27%) and ACCESSCORP (-0.52%), keeping the market in the green. Consequently, the year-to-date (YTD) return rose to 12.69%, while market capitalization gained N319.61bn to close at N25.95trn. Analysis of Wednesday’s market activities showed trade turnover settled lower relative to the previous session, with the value of transactions declining by 47.94%. A total of 349.56m shares valued at N3.70bn were exchanged in 4,587 deals. UNIVINSURE (+0.00%) led the volume chart with 73.05m units traded, while MTNN (+0.00%) led the value chart in deals worth N629.03m. Market breadth closed positive at a 1.33-to-1 ratio with advancing issues outnumbering declining ones. ETERNA (+10.00%) topped twenty-seven (27) others on the gainer’s log, while CWG (-9.28%) led twenty (20) others on the laggard’s table. 